This paper is about improving the speed of neural language models, which is a common topic in the natural language processing (NLP) field. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also introduces a novel algorithm that involves training a model end-to-end, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses clustering and prediction techniques, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV) fields. Finally, the paper mentions the use of the Gumbel softmax, which is a technique commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE).
